1. Unit Testing (smallest piece)
Test one function / one component
Example:
add(2,3) → 5

👉 Fast, isolated, but many tests needed

2. Integration Testing
Check if multiple parts work together
Example:
API + Database + Service layer

👉 Finds connection issues

3. System Testing
Test entire application
Example:
Login → Add to cart → Checkout

👉 Simulates real usage

4. End-to-End (E2E) Testing
Full user journey in real environment
Tools: Cypress, Playwright

👉 Slow but closest to reality

5. Regression Testing
Ensure new changes didn’t break old features

👉 Happens after every update

6. Performance Testing
Check speed, load, scalability

👉 “Can 10,000 users use it at once?”

7. Security Testing
Find vulnerabilities

👉 Prevent hacking